d 'LITDISCOVER': module for theory-aware literature review, analysis, and discovery
d
d   litdiscover combines latent Dirichlet allocation (LDA) topic
d modelling of abstract text with a deductive overlay of
d researcher- coded construct fields (theory, dependent variable,
d independent variable, moderator, mediator, decision, context,
d method, journal, year). It produces topic-by-field
d cross-tabulations, TCCM and ADO framework outputs,
d network-analytic measures (degree, betweenness, Louvain
d communities, modularity) over construct co-occurrences, FREX
d exclusivity scores, per-topic stability diagnostics via Jaccard
d similarity across random seeds, UMass coherence diagnostics, and
d a suite of static figures and interactive HTML deliverables
d (pyLDAvis, pyvis, plotly Sankey). Designed for systematic
d literature reviews across management, marketing, organisation
d studies, information systems, education, health policy, and the
d broader social and behavioural sciences. 
d
d KW: topic modelling
d KW: literature
d
d Requires: Stata version 19, heatplot, palettes, colrspace from SSC (q.v.), Python 3.10, Python packages
d
d Distribution-Date: 20260520
d
d Author: Nebojsa S. Davcik,  EM Normandie Business School, Oxford, UK
d Support: email davcik@@live.com
d
f litdiscover.ado
f litdiscover.sthlp
f litdi.ado
f litdiscover.py
f litdiscover_net.py
f litdiscover_viz.py
f litdiscover_example500.dta
